  "text": "While in their work they used background images to determine P (D [CITATION_1] but while in their formulation, the state of the voxel k is influenced only by the background state of the pixels in φ k i , in our formulation its state is also influenced by the pixels in χ k ij . While this property adds additional dependence between the voxels, it provides more information on the state of each voxel. In fact, we not only rely on the consensus observed in the voxel's footprint φ k i but also on the consensus observed in χ k ij . This allows us to recover from two kinds of situations, namely: when the colors of the foreground object are similar to the colors of the actual background points behind it, and when the information corresponding to the foreground object in the image R ij is missing. However, our approach will not help if the colors of the actual background points in χ k ij are also similar to the colors of the foreground element.",
